WEBVTT

00:09.143 --> 00:09.577
[Footsteps approach]

00:19.487 --> 00:20.788
Is she down?

00:20.821 --> 00:22.223
Yeah.

00:22.256 --> 00:24.492
Is it over?
Please tell me it's over.

00:24.525 --> 00:27.495
I love my parents,
but, good God...

00:27.528 --> 00:28.762
They're gone.

00:28.796 --> 00:31.532
In an hour,
they will be in the air

00:31.565 --> 00:34.435
on their way
back to Texas.

00:34.468 --> 00:36.537
They are gone.

00:36.570 --> 00:39.340
They are TWA's
problem now.

00:39.373 --> 00:40.808
[Moans]

00:40.841 --> 00:43.211
But, no. No!

00:43.244 --> 00:44.578
Why?!

00:44.612 --> 00:46.414
[Laughing]

00:48.316 --> 00:50.684
Oh, promise me we will
never look at each other

00:50.718 --> 00:52.220
the way they do.

00:52.253 --> 00:53.721
Mm. I can't promise.

00:53.754 --> 00:55.156
[Chuckles]

00:55.189 --> 00:57.791
Sorry they drive you
so crazy.

00:57.825 --> 01:00.528
What are you talking about?
They were great.

01:00.561 --> 01:02.696
You see
what your dad got me?

01:02.730 --> 01:05.599
The perfect reminder

01:05.633 --> 01:07.735
of how unmanly he thinks I am.

01:07.768 --> 01:10.304
[Electric knife whirring]
-Oh! Screechy.

01:10.338 --> 01:12.240
Yeah, why we need
to improve upon a tool

01:12.273 --> 01:14.175
that's been serving mankind
brilliantly

01:14.208 --> 01:16.277
for millions of years
is beyond me.

01:16.310 --> 01:18.179
[Electric knife whirring]

01:18.212 --> 01:19.180
Dang.

01:19.213 --> 01:20.814
This baby's really sharp.

01:20.848 --> 01:22.250
Hey,
give me an old boot.

01:22.283 --> 01:23.617
Let's see
what this thing can do.

01:23.651 --> 01:25.386
Stop it.
You're gonna wake her up.

01:25.419 --> 01:27.288
Oh, fine.

01:27.321 --> 01:28.689
Oh.

01:28.722 --> 01:31.125
I'm always amazed
at what my mom can do

01:31.159 --> 01:33.361
with a glass of Chardonnay
in her hand.

01:33.394 --> 01:34.762
She could join the circus.

01:34.795 --> 01:36.497
Hey, you think
they had fun?

01:36.530 --> 01:39.133
Yeah.

01:39.167 --> 01:41.302
I'm not sure my mom
approved of the building,

01:41.335 --> 01:43.404
or the neighborhood
for that matter, but...

01:43.437 --> 01:46.507
you know, it's all about
appearances to her.

01:46.540 --> 01:48.442
Yeah. And did you hear
what your dad said

01:48.476 --> 01:49.710
about the peanut farmer

01:49.743 --> 01:51.845
and his whole
energy-conservation diatribe?

01:51.879 --> 01:53.414
No, don't. I can't.

01:53.447 --> 01:55.316
Or the line about how we
should live in an area

01:55.349 --> 01:57.151
with more homeowners
than renters.

01:57.185 --> 01:58.652
You know
what that's code for.

01:58.686 --> 02:01.422
Well...at least
they're good with Joanie.

02:01.455 --> 02:02.890
Your mom
is great with her.

02:02.923 --> 02:04.725
Well, so is my dad.

02:04.758 --> 02:07.695
I mean, he didn't strike the
child, if that's what you mean.

02:07.728 --> 02:10.298
Yeah, he also managed
not to set off any fireworks

02:10.331 --> 02:11.632
next to her head.

02:11.665 --> 02:12.666
[Chuckles]

02:12.700 --> 02:14.435
It was one bottle rocket.

02:14.468 --> 02:16.337
Oh, my God.
Did you see the look on his face

02:16.370 --> 02:19.207
when Joanie spit up
on his special 4th of July Polo?

02:19.240 --> 02:21.742
Hey, she was doing
that shirt a favor.

02:21.775 --> 02:25.446
Oh, he tries to help.
He just doesn't always know how.

02:25.479 --> 02:29.583
Offering to buy us a house
as long as it's in Dallas.

02:29.617 --> 02:32.586
Oh, come on. I mean, would it be
the worst thing in the world

02:32.620 --> 02:34.222
if we had
a little bit of help?

02:34.255 --> 02:35.756
We don't need help.

02:35.789 --> 02:38.592
Why? Do you want to
live here forever?

02:38.626 --> 02:43.697
Look, Donna, we are not gonna
live here forever, okay?

02:43.731 --> 02:48.402
Okay, we're gonna build
something, a machine, okay?

02:48.436 --> 02:51.539
And we're gonna sell it
together.

02:51.572 --> 02:53.841
Oh, yeah?
And when are we gonna do that?

02:53.874 --> 02:55.776
Between nursing
and changing diapers

02:55.809 --> 02:58.546
and being the only one that
can get the baby to sleep,

02:58.579 --> 03:00.548
I don't really see
a whole lot of time

03:00.581 --> 03:02.483
for building computers
in my future.

03:02.516 --> 03:05.286
Gordon: Yeah, well, it's not
always gonna be like that.

03:05.319 --> 03:06.254
-Oh, yeah?
-Yeah.

03:06.287 --> 03:07.421
What's gonna change?

03:07.455 --> 03:09.790
I don't know.
I mean, everything.

03:09.823 --> 03:12.393
Well, I hope so, 'cause I don't
want to be breastfeeding

03:12.426 --> 03:13.994
and doing dishes
the rest of my life.

03:14.027 --> 03:15.996
Look,
it's been three months.

03:16.029 --> 03:18.799
Well, in Texas,
I'd be freed up to go to work,

03:18.832 --> 03:20.834
and so would you.

03:20.868 --> 03:24.738
We're not actually talking about
moving back to Texas right now.

03:24.772 --> 03:26.807
My mom said that
if we wanted --

03:26.840 --> 03:28.342
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

03:28.376 --> 03:30.444
You've been talking
to your mom about this?

03:30.478 --> 03:32.913
Well --
What, are you guys
making plans?

03:32.946 --> 03:35.416
No, just...in broad,
hypothetical terms.

03:35.449 --> 03:37.518
N-No, no, no, Donna!
Listen to me!

03:37.551 --> 03:39.787
This industry is
all about who we know,

03:39.820 --> 03:41.755
and if we leave,
we'll miss it.

03:41.789 --> 03:43.691
Okay. That's not help.
Okay. That's --

03:43.724 --> 03:45.526
That's offering
to kill us slowly.

03:45.559 --> 03:47.428
That's a death sentence.
-No, they just --

03:47.461 --> 03:49.530
They're seeing that we're
struggling is all.

03:49.563 --> 03:51.732
Well, I'll do more, okay?
I-I-I'll help!

03:51.765 --> 03:53.301
Oh, yeah?

03:53.334 --> 03:55.636
Every time the baby cries,
you hand her back to me.

03:55.669 --> 03:57.338
Okay. Well,
I won't do that.

03:57.371 --> 03:58.706
Well, it's not just that.

03:58.739 --> 04:00.608
It's -- I'm concerned
about everything

04:00.641 --> 04:02.843
that she sees
and eats and touches.

04:02.876 --> 04:05.479
And you -- you're exploding
fireworks next to her head.

04:05.513 --> 04:06.847
Oh, my God.

04:06.880 --> 04:09.583
Donna, it was one
goddamn bottle rocket, okay?

04:09.617 --> 04:10.918
Look,
if you want to leave,

04:10.951 --> 04:12.686
let's just pack everything up
right now.

04:12.720 --> 04:13.787
No, I'm serious!

04:13.821 --> 04:15.523
Let's pack
everything up right now,

04:15.556 --> 04:17.558
and we'll move back to Texas,
and I'll go get a job

04:17.591 --> 04:19.293
working for one
of your dad's friends,

04:19.327 --> 04:21.362
and you can go play golf
with your mom every day.

04:21.395 --> 04:22.830
That's
what you think I want?

04:22.863 --> 04:24.632
I don't know
what the hell you want.

04:24.665 --> 04:26.400
Okay, yesterday it was --
it was me

04:26.434 --> 04:28.502
and -- and San Francisco
and building something,

04:28.536 --> 04:30.070
and today, I -- I
don't have a clue!

04:30.103 --> 04:32.306
You are being
so mean right now.

04:32.340 --> 04:34.442
I would just like us
to stop and think

04:34.475 --> 04:36.577
about one thing
we do before we do it.

04:36.610 --> 04:39.079
I mean, we got -- we got
pregnant and then married,

04:39.112 --> 04:40.714
and then we got
this whole life...

04:40.748 --> 04:42.483
[Joanie cries]
...and I feel like
I haven't made

04:42.516 --> 04:43.884
any of the decisions
to get us here.

04:43.917 --> 04:45.653
Oh, you feel like you didn't
make any decisions?

04:45.686 --> 04:47.788
Was I the one who got down on
one knee and proposed to you?

04:47.821 --> 04:49.523
Oh, God.

04:49.557 --> 04:53.627
[Crying continues]

04:53.661 --> 04:55.796
Oh. I guess
I'll go get her, then.

04:55.829 --> 04:57.498
No, just let her cry!

04:57.531 --> 04:59.400
[Crying continues]

04:59.433 --> 05:00.701
[Door slams]

05:03.371 --> 05:05.373
Mommy's here.
It's okay.

05:05.406 --> 05:07.841
[Crying continues]

05:16.917 --> 05:19.052
[Keys rattle]

05:27.495 --> 05:30.631
[Joanie crying]

05:32.566 --> 05:35.469
Donna:
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

05:35.503 --> 05:37.971
I know.

05:38.005 --> 05:40.374
I know, I know.

05:40.408 --> 05:41.909
It's okay.

05:41.942 --> 05:42.976
[Crying]

05:43.010 --> 05:44.578
Oh, baby.

05:44.612 --> 05:46.079
Hey.

05:46.113 --> 05:48.148
Hey.

05:48.181 --> 05:50.083
Hey.

05:50.117 --> 05:51.519
Hey.

05:51.552 --> 05:53.387
It's okay.

05:53.421 --> 05:55.456
You want
your little elephant? Huh?

05:55.489 --> 05:58.526
Yeah.
It's not so bad.

05:58.559 --> 06:01.762
It's not so bad.

06:01.795 --> 06:03.997
Okay.

06:14.475 --> 06:17.044
[Door bells jingle]

06:18.712 --> 06:21.449
[Pay phone dings]

06:24.718 --> 06:28.388
[Car door opens, engine starts]

06:33.694 --> 06:36.797
[Engine revs, car departs]

06:41.134 --> 06:43.036
[Semitruck engine starts]

06:54.782 --> 06:56.650
[Engine starts]

