08:00.548 --> 08:03.116
[Door opens]

08:03.150 --> 08:05.553
I don't understand
what the rush is.

08:05.586 --> 08:07.988
The rush is I want to
get this over with.

08:08.021 --> 08:11.124
I don't want to be making
a million trips back here.

08:11.158 --> 08:14.194
So, whatever you want,
you should get today.

08:14.227 --> 08:15.195
[Door closes]

08:15.228 --> 08:17.665
Hold on.

08:19.600 --> 08:22.636
So, for big stuff, furniture
we can't move ourselves,

08:22.670 --> 08:26.106
green means keep,
red means donate.

08:26.139 --> 08:28.742
Okay?
Green, yes, red, no.

08:28.776 --> 08:30.644
Okay. Got it.

08:30.678 --> 08:32.646
Start in your rooms.

08:32.680 --> 08:36.316
Don't forget all your
schoolwork, textbooks.

08:36.349 --> 08:38.719
Hey, guys?

08:40.921 --> 08:42.790
I love you.

08:42.823 --> 08:44.057
Love you, too.

08:44.091 --> 08:46.560
I love you.

08:55.002 --> 08:57.137
Okay.

09:08.115 --> 09:09.783
[Drawer opens]

09:23.997 --> 09:26.166
[Doorbell rings]

09:28.702 --> 09:31.705
[Sighs]

09:31.739 --> 09:33.607
Hey, guys.

09:33.641 --> 09:35.609
Oh, hey, hey.

09:35.643 --> 09:37.645
How are the girls doing?

09:37.678 --> 09:41.114
That's a stupid question.
We're all doing terrible.

09:41.148 --> 09:43.250
Everyone's terrible.

09:43.283 --> 09:45.352
How are you doing?

09:45.385 --> 09:47.655
[Scoffs]

09:47.688 --> 09:50.223
You know.

09:50.257 --> 09:52.125
Uh, thanks
for helping out.

09:52.159 --> 09:53.694
It's...

09:53.727 --> 09:55.162
Of course.

09:55.195 --> 09:59.199
Uh...
the service...was beautiful.

09:59.232 --> 10:01.201
[Truck door closes]
-Yeah.

10:01.234 --> 10:03.370
I thought what you said
was really nice.

10:03.403 --> 10:05.072
Do you have
a copy of that?

10:05.105 --> 10:07.007
I'd love to save it
for the girls.

10:07.040 --> 10:08.075
I do.

10:08.108 --> 10:09.076
Thanks.

10:09.109 --> 10:10.343
Hey.

10:16.283 --> 10:20.253
I wanted to say how beautiful
the service was.

10:20.287 --> 10:22.155
Like, really personal.

10:22.189 --> 10:23.891
Thanks.

10:25.959 --> 10:28.929
So, what, um...

10:28.962 --> 10:30.230
Where would
you like us
to start?

10:30.263 --> 10:32.700
Yeah, God,
it's, uh...

10:32.733 --> 10:34.034
kind of hard
to figure out.

10:34.067 --> 10:36.436
Maybe you could tackle
Gordon's closet?

10:36.469 --> 10:38.171
Just, you know,
throw his clothes

10:38.205 --> 10:39.807
in garbage bags
for Goodwill.

10:44.311 --> 10:46.279
Yes.

10:54.421 --> 10:57.157
I'm gonna start
in the kitchen.

10:57.190 --> 10:59.426
If you wanted to pack up
everything in here,

10:59.459 --> 11:00.761
that'd be great.

11:00.794 --> 11:02.429
Yeah.

11:03.864 --> 11:05.132
Oh, I'd just, you know,

11:05.165 --> 11:06.834
keep all the pictures
for the girls, I think.

11:06.867 --> 11:08.401
They'll probably want them
eventually.

11:08.435 --> 11:10.403
Oh, of course.
Yeah, right.

11:11.905 --> 11:14.708
[Sighs]

11:22.783 --> 11:25.252
Hey, uh...could you put
something on?

11:25.285 --> 11:26.820
What?

11:26.854 --> 11:29.456
Oh, it's too quiet.
Just something, anything?

11:29.489 --> 11:31.158
Yeah, uh...yeah.

11:49.843 --> 11:51.879
[Utensils clatter]

12:13.233 --> 12:14.968
[Scoffs]
I don't know. Sorry.

12:15.002 --> 12:16.503
Nothing feels right.

12:21.975 --> 12:24.077
This is perfect.

