[Knock on door]

16:12.172 --> 16:14.207
Check this out.

16:14.241 --> 16:16.343
[Laughing] Oh.

16:16.376 --> 16:18.311
He loved this one.

16:18.345 --> 16:21.314
This is from when we went to
that pumpkin patch in Garland.

16:21.348 --> 16:22.582
Mm-hmm.

16:22.615 --> 16:24.584
Can you believe
there was a time

16:24.617 --> 16:27.154
that you got this excited
about pumpkins?

16:27.187 --> 16:29.256
I still get excited
about pumpkins.

16:29.289 --> 16:31.291
Pumpkins blow my mind.

16:36.229 --> 16:38.765
You know, you don't have to get
rid of anything.

16:38.798 --> 16:41.268
You could just...
pack up your whole room.

16:42.335 --> 16:45.772
[Sighs] No, it's just,
I don't know where to start.

16:46.839 --> 16:48.475
You need some help?

16:50.477 --> 16:52.045
Yeah.

16:52.079 --> 16:54.381
Let's start with your clothes.
That's easy.

16:54.414 --> 16:56.516
Okay.

16:59.619 --> 17:02.355
Oh, man.

17:02.389 --> 17:05.125
So, just everything?

17:05.158 --> 17:07.627
Yeah. I think so.

17:24.111 --> 17:25.812
What's this?

17:28.615 --> 17:30.350
USC?

17:30.383 --> 17:31.851
Northwestern?
-Um...

17:31.884 --> 17:33.786
What are these?
Are these duplicates?

17:33.820 --> 17:35.455
You did send in
your applications?

17:35.488 --> 17:37.390
I don't want to talk about this
right now, okay?

17:37.424 --> 17:38.558
We are talking about this.

17:38.591 --> 17:40.293
We're talking about this
right now.

17:40.327 --> 17:41.461
Where are you going?

17:49.302 --> 17:51.271
Leave me alone.

17:51.304 --> 17:52.805
You told us
that you sent these.

17:52.839 --> 17:54.141
What's going on?

17:54.174 --> 17:56.176
Well, I didn't.

17:56.209 --> 17:58.345
Can we talk about this
privately? Please?

17:58.378 --> 17:59.779
Why? Why?

17:59.812 --> 18:03.550
Why not here? Huh?
Why don't you let them see?

18:04.717 --> 18:06.786
Why? Are you afraid
of what they might think?

18:06.819 --> 18:08.888
That's enough.
Let's go outside.

18:08.921 --> 18:11.558
No! Let them see
what a mess we've been!

18:11.591 --> 18:13.760
And we have been.

18:13.793 --> 18:16.429
I don't know why
you're doing this.

18:16.463 --> 18:20.300
Your father would be --
he'd be devastated.

18:20.333 --> 18:23.770
Well, it's a good thing that
he's not here to see it, then.

18:23.803 --> 18:25.205
Oh!

18:26.673 --> 18:28.475
That's...

18:28.508 --> 18:32.145
That is --
That's a horrible thing to say.

18:32.179 --> 18:36.316
How long did it take you
to use Dad against me?

18:36.349 --> 18:37.717
Huh?

18:37.750 --> 18:39.486
Like 10 days?

18:40.620 --> 18:43.890
I'm surprised that you could
hold out that long.

18:43.923 --> 18:45.692
[Door slams]

18:45.725 --> 18:48.795
You are...

18:48.828 --> 18:51.698
Sometimes I don't even know
who you are anymore.

18:51.731 --> 18:54.434
We're all hurting.
We're all upset.

18:54.467 --> 18:56.436
What do you know?

18:56.469 --> 18:59.472
You couldn't even stand him.

19:04.377 --> 19:06.646
[Footsteps departing]

19:06.679 --> 19:08.415
[Door slams]

19:17.224 --> 19:17.957
Cameron: Hey.
Joe took the first load.

19:19.626 --> 19:21.361
Do you smell that?

19:22.562 --> 19:24.731
Cigarette smoke.

19:24.764 --> 19:26.299
I'm gonna kill her.

19:26.333 --> 19:28.635
She wants to
piss you off.

19:28.668 --> 19:32.472
Okay? It's the exact same thing
I would've done when I was 17.

19:32.505 --> 19:36.309
I did my fair share of teenage
bullshit, but this is --

19:36.343 --> 19:39.779
She wants to be a jerk.
Just let her be a jerk.

19:39.812 --> 19:42.482
I don't know that
that's a strong enough word

19:42.515 --> 19:43.683
for what she's being.

19:43.716 --> 19:47.287
I mean,
she lost it at me.

19:47.320 --> 19:48.888
Donna: She's the one
who didn't send them in.

19:48.921 --> 19:50.823
Yeah.

19:50.857 --> 19:53.726
I don't know if reason's
gonna be that helpful to you

19:53.760 --> 19:57.330
in this situation...
or her.

19:57.364 --> 19:59.198
[Sighs]

20:01.968 --> 20:04.537
Probably shouldn't have
brought up Gordon.

20:06.038 --> 20:08.408
Probably not.

20:12.345 --> 20:15.482
I mean, was it not clear that
she disrespected me or --

20:15.515 --> 20:17.350
Could I talk to her?

20:17.384 --> 20:18.685
Yeah.

20:21.754 --> 20:24.591
Tell her she's being
an asshole.

20:26.659 --> 20:27.894
[Knock on door]

20:27.927 --> 20:29.862
Do not open the door.

20:29.896 --> 20:31.498
Whoops.

20:34.401 --> 20:35.535
Hey.

20:35.568 --> 20:36.603
Mm.

20:36.636 --> 20:37.970
Really good one.

20:38.004 --> 20:40.407
Your mom's totally
freaking out right now.

20:40.440 --> 20:42.375
Yeah.

20:42.409 --> 20:44.611
You don't get a million points
for subtlety,

20:44.644 --> 20:46.413
but still,
it's very effective.

20:46.446 --> 20:48.648
Mm. I wasn't trying
to do anything.

20:48.681 --> 20:49.949
I just needed a smoke.

20:58.625 --> 21:00.560
Mm.

21:02.429 --> 21:03.996
[Water sizzles]

21:07.967 --> 21:09.736
What's up?

21:09.769 --> 21:12.872
[Door opens, closes]

21:12.905 --> 21:14.006
Joe: Hello?

21:14.040 --> 21:16.609
In here.

21:20.413 --> 21:21.648
Where is everyone?

21:21.681 --> 21:23.383
Oh...

21:23.416 --> 21:26.653
scattered to the far corners
of the house,

21:26.686 --> 21:31.290
some avoiding me,
others also avoiding me.

21:34.661 --> 21:36.563
Do I smell
cigarettes smoke?

21:36.596 --> 21:39.098
You do.

21:39.131 --> 21:40.667
[Chuckles] Joanie?

21:40.700 --> 21:42.335
Uh-huh.

21:45.605 --> 21:48.908
How are you holding up?

21:48.941 --> 21:50.743
Haley: What the hell?

21:50.777 --> 21:52.645
Sweetie, what's wrong?

21:52.679 --> 21:54.414
Dad's clothes,
where are they?

21:54.447 --> 21:56.549
Oh, I just got back
from Goodwill.

21:56.583 --> 21:57.950
Oh.

21:57.984 --> 21:59.886
Honey, what's wrong?
Talk to me.

21:59.919 --> 22:02.855
Dad's s-sweater,
I wanted to keep it, but...

22:02.889 --> 22:05.057
It's the green one.
It doesn't matter.

22:05.091 --> 22:06.526
I'll...
Forget it.

22:06.559 --> 22:08.528
No, no.
I just got back.

22:08.561 --> 22:10.630
You want
your dad's sweater?

22:12.465 --> 22:14.100
We're gonna go get it.

22:14.133 --> 22:15.735
Come on.

22:17.837 --> 22:20.039
[Door opens, closes]

22:20.072 --> 22:22.041
I bet she's more upset
about the fact

22:22.074 --> 22:23.910
that she has to tell her friends
I'm not going to college

22:23.943 --> 22:25.044
than the fact that
I'm not going.

22:25.077 --> 22:27.013
Oh, Joanie, come on.

22:27.046 --> 22:28.648
You know that's not true.

22:28.681 --> 22:30.016
Everything's
appearances with her.

22:30.049 --> 22:32.552
"Look at my perfect house
and my perfect pool

22:32.585 --> 22:34.621
and my perfect daughters."

22:34.654 --> 22:36.523
Did you know
she irons her jeans?

22:36.556 --> 22:38.491
Okay.

22:38.525 --> 22:41.093
Don't say things
you can't take back.

22:45.532 --> 22:47.500
[Clears throat]

22:47.534 --> 22:49.669
I need you
to give her a break.

22:49.702 --> 22:51.771
Give her a break?

22:51.804 --> 22:53.906
Yeah.
You know why?

22:53.940 --> 22:56.976
You're hard to navigate
because you're a dick.

22:57.009 --> 23:00.480
And I say that
because I'm a dick.

23:00.513 --> 23:02.582
I'm, like, huge.

23:02.615 --> 23:05.051
I'm Queen Big Dick.
Like...

23:05.084 --> 23:06.553
That sounded weird,
but...

23:06.586 --> 23:09.722
-Yeah.
-...the point is, you two...

23:09.756 --> 23:13.159
Just try and understand
where your mom's coming from.

23:13.192 --> 23:15.962
And vice versa,
of course!

23:15.995 --> 23:18.030
But, look,
when I was your age,

23:18.064 --> 23:20.500
I cut my mom
out of my life, and...

23:20.533 --> 23:22.502
you don't want to do that.

23:22.535 --> 23:24.971
I mean,
I had a good reason to.

23:25.004 --> 23:26.573
My mom was a mess.

23:26.606 --> 23:28.608
Like, missed my graduation

23:28.641 --> 23:30.910
'cause she drank too much
mouthwash kind of a mess.

23:30.943 --> 23:32.211
But still...

23:32.244 --> 23:34.113
[Sighs]

23:34.146 --> 23:36.849
It's time
you can't get back.

23:38.751 --> 23:41.588
I could stay with you.

23:43.656 --> 23:45.725
The two of us
in my tin can?

23:45.758 --> 23:48.528
Yeah. I could get another
trailer and take it out there.

23:48.561 --> 23:49.662
It'd be awesome.

23:49.696 --> 23:51.698
Oh, Joanie...

23:51.731 --> 23:53.966
I mean, I can't even
take care of a plant.

23:54.000 --> 23:55.668
[Chuckles]

23:55.702 --> 23:57.704
I don't need to be
taken care of.

23:57.737 --> 23:59.205
God.

23:59.238 --> 24:01.808
Everyone looks at me like
I can't do anything for myself,

24:01.841 --> 24:03.643
like I'm in diapers.
-Okay. I'm sorry.

24:03.676 --> 24:05.612
That -- That's really
not what I meant.

24:05.645 --> 24:07.179
I just mean...

24:07.213 --> 24:11.117
This is why college
is so great.

24:11.150 --> 24:14.787
You get to go and be by yourself
for the first time,

24:14.821 --> 24:17.056
you can do whatever
you want to do,

24:17.089 --> 24:19.058
smoke whatever
you want to smoke,

24:19.091 --> 24:20.793
learn about the things
that interest you,

24:20.827 --> 24:22.228
and if you don't know
what those are,

24:22.261 --> 24:23.730
you -- you get to
figure it out.

24:23.763 --> 24:24.897
I mean,
it's the perfect --

24:24.931 --> 24:26.132
I know.

24:27.600 --> 24:29.602
I know.

24:37.577 --> 24:39.245
Joe: Hey, you want to put
something on?

24:39.278 --> 24:40.680
What?

24:40.713 --> 24:42.615
You don't have to listen
to your thing.

24:42.649 --> 24:44.851
You can play it
on the stereo.

24:44.884 --> 24:46.653
No.
You wouldn't like it.

24:47.720 --> 24:49.989
I'm not that old.

24:50.022 --> 24:51.090
Put it on.

24:51.123 --> 24:53.793
[Cassette rattles]

24:53.826 --> 24:55.194
[Barnes & Barnes'
"Fish Heads" plays ]

24:55.227 --> 24:57.296
* Fish heads, fish heads

24:57.329 --> 24:59.732
* Roly-poly fish heads

24:59.766 --> 25:02.101
* Fish heads, fish heads

25:02.134 --> 25:04.203
* Eat them up, yum

25:04.236 --> 25:07.640
* Ask a fish head any...

25:09.809 --> 25:11.678
How'd it go?

25:11.711 --> 25:15.014
Uh, good.
She's coolly awesome.

25:15.047 --> 25:17.283
Managed to swipe these.

25:17.316 --> 25:19.819
Hey.

25:22.354 --> 25:25.124
Uh, these are Gordon's
grandmother's.

25:25.157 --> 25:27.960
Gonna save them
for the girls.

25:27.994 --> 25:29.796
Christ, I keep saying that.

25:29.829 --> 25:32.765
I don't even know if they'll
care about any of this stuff.

25:32.799 --> 25:34.333
They will.

25:34.366 --> 25:37.169
Yeah, or they'll just...
put them in a box,

25:37.203 --> 25:39.972
put the box in the attic,
and then, when they die,

25:40.006 --> 25:41.774
their kids will pull it out
and say,

25:41.808 --> 25:43.776
"I guess we should save this
for our kids."

25:43.810 --> 25:46.012
Yeah, that's, uh...

25:46.045 --> 25:48.180
pretty dark.

25:50.950 --> 25:52.685
I finished the game.

25:52.719 --> 25:56.122
What game?

25:56.155 --> 25:59.058
Your game, "Pilgrim."

26:01.127 --> 26:03.830
Uh...wow.

26:05.264 --> 26:06.933
You "finished it"
finished it?

26:06.966 --> 26:09.135
Yeah, finally.
You made it hard enough.

26:09.168 --> 26:11.871
Yeah, I made it
for people like you.

26:13.740 --> 26:18.645
Unfortunately, there aren't many
people like you anymore.

26:18.678 --> 26:20.680
[Chuckles]

26:23.716 --> 26:25.952
Well, I liked
the way it ended.

26:25.985 --> 26:28.655
The pilgrim was a kid.

26:29.822 --> 26:33.325
Yeah,
the pilgrim was a kid.

26:35.327 --> 26:37.063
[Laughs]

26:37.096 --> 26:39.832
Thank you for playing it.

26:39.866 --> 26:41.668
Uh...

26:41.701 --> 26:43.670
Yeah, it means a lot.

26:45.772 --> 26:48.407
Hey, uh...

26:48.440 --> 26:50.677
at the hospital, with Bos,

26:50.710 --> 26:53.112
what I said,
I-I-I didn't mean it.

26:53.145 --> 26:56.683
Please, Donna, I don't even
remember what you said.

26:57.984 --> 26:59.652
Uh, yeah.

26:59.686 --> 27:01.788
Um, I just mean
that I, you know...

27:01.821 --> 27:03.656
me, I've been
in such a fog.

27:03.690 --> 27:05.191
I can't even remember
my own name, let alo--

27:05.224 --> 27:07.894
Yeah, no. Me too.

27:07.927 --> 27:10.062
I'm gonna, uh,
go get another box.

27:19.872 --> 27:20.206
Let's just go.

27:23.375 --> 27:25.311
No.

27:28.047 --> 27:29.782
Oh, here.
Is this it?

27:29.816 --> 27:30.950
-No.
-Hey, hey, hey.

27:30.983 --> 27:33.152
You can't be doing that.
What...

27:33.185 --> 27:35.121
No.

27:35.154 --> 27:37.757
We just dropped these off
an hour ago.

27:37.790 --> 27:40.326
We, uh, put something
in here by mistake.

27:40.359 --> 27:43.696
Man: Well, once you drop it off,
it's our property.

27:43.730 --> 27:47.033
You know, I have no way of
verifying what's what or...

27:47.066 --> 27:50.069
-These are just T-shirts.
-...or who's whatever and so on.

27:50.102 --> 27:51.971
Let's go.

27:52.004 --> 27:54.774
Okay. These clothes
belonged to a friend of mine,

27:54.807 --> 27:57.343
and he's no longer with us.

27:57.376 --> 28:01.380
There's exactly one item of
clothing that we're looking for.

28:01.413 --> 28:03.950
We dropped off nine bags.

28:03.983 --> 28:06.252
There's only eight here.

28:06.285 --> 28:09.822
That sweater's in the ninth bag,
and we just have to find it.

28:11.858 --> 28:14.761
Yeah, I mean, all this stuff
belonged to somebody, man.

28:16.963 --> 28:18.430
There it is.

28:18.464 --> 28:19.465
Hmm?

28:19.498 --> 28:21.000
That's our bag
right there.

28:21.033 --> 28:23.035
How could you know that?
You can't know that.

28:23.069 --> 28:25.237
Look at that bag!
Now look at these bags.

28:25.271 --> 28:26.973
Okay. They look like
trash bags, man.

28:27.006 --> 28:28.507
I-I-I don't know
what to tell you.

28:28.540 --> 28:30.142
I'm sorry.
-That's our bag!

28:30.176 --> 28:31.811
It's just, this is
company policy, man.

28:31.844 --> 28:32.812
I don't know what to say.

28:32.845 --> 28:34.246
Let's go.

28:34.280 --> 28:36.816
It is
what it is, man.

28:44.190 --> 28:46.458
[Gravel crunching]

28:46.492 --> 28:48.294
You've got your learner's
permit, right?

28:48.327 --> 28:49.762
Yeah.

28:49.796 --> 28:52.899
Pull the truck up.
Keep it running.

28:52.932 --> 28:54.801
Okay.

28:54.834 --> 28:56.102
[Car approaches]

28:56.135 --> 28:57.403
[Engine shuts off]

28:57.436 --> 28:59.471
[Car door opens, closes]
-Hey.

29:01.540 --> 29:02.875
How you doing?

29:02.909 --> 29:04.243
Super.

29:04.276 --> 29:05.411
[Sighs]

29:05.444 --> 29:06.478
Hi.

29:06.512 --> 29:08.480
[Chuckles]

29:08.514 --> 29:09.481
Mm.

29:09.515 --> 29:11.017
Are you going somewhere?

29:11.050 --> 29:13.052
I'm moving.

29:13.085 --> 29:15.454
Got some friends
in Seattle.

29:15.487 --> 29:18.124
I'm gonna give that a try.
They say it's great.

29:18.157 --> 29:21.894
Yeah, yeah, I heard it's,
um...a whole scene.

29:21.928 --> 29:23.262
Yeah.

29:23.295 --> 29:25.231
I didn't know
you were going.

29:25.264 --> 29:29.101
I told Joe and everybody
a couple days ago.

29:29.135 --> 29:32.371
I, uh...
Sort of a quick decision.

29:32.404 --> 29:34.206
I -- I'm sorry that I --

29:34.240 --> 29:38.310
I couldn't stick it out there,
for Joe's sake, but, um...

29:38.344 --> 29:41.113
There's just too much
of Gordon there at Comet,

29:41.147 --> 29:43.916
and there's too much of Gordon
everywhere here.

29:43.950 --> 29:45.451
Yeah.

29:45.484 --> 29:50.256
Hey, you know, doesn't,
uh, sound that bad.

29:50.289 --> 29:52.258
Car full of stuff,
a clean slate...

29:52.291 --> 29:54.326
I suppose.

29:54.360 --> 29:56.195
I've pinballed
around a bunch.

29:56.228 --> 29:57.930
When I landed at Comet,

29:57.964 --> 30:00.900
I thought that maybe I was
done with all that, but...

30:00.933 --> 30:03.903
perhaps Seattle
will stick.

30:05.504 --> 30:07.874
Do you know what's
gonna happen with it?

30:09.541 --> 30:13.179
Oh, Comet. Uh...

30:13.212 --> 30:16.548
I -- I think Joe will,
you know, carry it on.

30:16.582 --> 30:18.284
I guess.

30:18.317 --> 30:19.485
I hope so.

30:19.518 --> 30:21.587
He really loves it.

30:21.620 --> 30:23.489
With everything he's lost,

30:23.522 --> 30:26.158
it'd be a shame
if that went, too.

30:26.192 --> 30:28.227
Yeah.

30:28.260 --> 30:30.396
I'm gonna go inside.

30:34.333 --> 30:36.068
[Brakes squeal]

30:36.102 --> 30:38.137
[Engine idling]

30:49.048 --> 30:50.516
Go, go! Let's go!

30:50.549 --> 30:51.583
Come on, man!

30:51.617 --> 30:53.285
Go, go!
Go, go, go!

30:53.319 --> 30:55.587
[Tires screech]

30:55.621 --> 30:58.190
What is this?

30:58.224 --> 30:59.926
[Splashing]

30:59.959 --> 31:01.327
[Tires screech]

31:04.396 --> 31:07.166
[Both laugh]

31:07.199 --> 31:09.501
Haley: Holy shit.

31:09.535 --> 31:13.139
[Laughing continues]

31:20.179 --> 31:23.649
Possible that I --
I got the wrong bag.

31:23.682 --> 31:27.219
[Laughs] Well, I -- I don't
think we can go back.

31:27.253 --> 31:29.621
[Both laugh]

31:52.945 --> 31:54.513
Oh, I, uh...thought you might
want to have this, so, uh...

32:00.619 --> 32:03.722
Uh, yeah,
we had a lot of fun.

32:03.755 --> 32:08.260
Gordon
was up for anything.

32:08.294 --> 32:10.696
I mean,
I don't have to tell you.

32:10.729 --> 32:12.965
[Chuckles] Yeah.

32:12.999 --> 32:18.170
Well, he was just...
crazy about you.

32:22.274 --> 32:25.177
It was a beautiful service,
by the way.

32:25.211 --> 32:28.547
Yeah.
Yeah, I thought so, too.

32:30.349 --> 32:36.288
Hey, uh, if there's anything
here that you'd like to have,

32:36.322 --> 32:39.091
you should, you know,
please feel free.

32:39.125 --> 32:41.427
Oh, uh, thanks.

32:41.460 --> 32:45.531
I don't...really like
his decorating style.

32:45.564 --> 32:46.632
[Laughs]

32:46.665 --> 32:48.734
I never told him that.

32:48.767 --> 32:53.639
It's, like, were you a vaquero
in a past life or something?

32:53.672 --> 32:55.141
[Laughs] Yeah, I think, uh --

32:55.174 --> 32:56.742
I think he had
a decorator do it --

32:56.775 --> 33:00.046
a decorator with a fetish
for Navajo blankets.

33:00.079 --> 33:02.014
[Chuckles]

33:03.449 --> 33:05.651
You know
what picture I love?

33:05.684 --> 33:10.222
There's this great one
of the two of you.

33:10.256 --> 33:13.659
You're young,
and I don't know how old,

33:13.692 --> 33:16.695
but you're both
holding beers and...

33:16.728 --> 33:19.765
Gordon's got these
wild sideburns.

33:19.798 --> 33:22.034
Yeah, yeah, I know it.

33:22.068 --> 33:26.538
You both look like --
oh, man -- like -- like,

33:26.572 --> 33:28.407
"Look out, world."

33:31.810 --> 33:37.149
As soon as we got together,
I got very, you know,

33:37.183 --> 33:40.286
"That's mine.
I want him all to myself.

33:40.319 --> 33:43.255
I want all the Gordon
there is."

33:43.289 --> 33:46.092
But you already had
so much of him...

33:46.125 --> 33:51.663
You had...
hell-raising sideburns Gordon

33:51.697 --> 33:53.732
and who knows what else.

33:53.765 --> 33:55.801
And it made me jealous.

33:57.436 --> 33:58.704
Well...

33:58.737 --> 34:00.672
I don't -- I don't know
what I'm saying.

34:00.706 --> 34:03.209
Uh...

34:03.242 --> 34:05.644
Goddamn, Gordon,
what the hell?

34:10.316 --> 34:13.485
Well, I'm gonna...
get out of your hair.

34:13.519 --> 34:15.787
Thank you.

34:15.821 --> 34:20.326
Joanie's, uh, up in her room
if you wanted to say hi.

34:20.359 --> 34:24.330
But I would, um...
proceed with caution.

34:24.363 --> 34:27.766
Thanks.
I'll be careful.

34:42.414 --> 34:44.250
Joe's been gone
for a while, huh?

34:44.283 --> 34:46.752
Yeah, maybe they stopped
to get something to eat.

34:46.785 --> 34:49.855
That's good. Haley needs to get
out of here for a little while.

34:49.888 --> 34:52.658
Joe's been so great
with her.

34:52.691 --> 34:57.529
Hey, uh, did you want the weird
priest statues or...?

34:57.563 --> 35:00.532
You know, I already have
so many of them at home.

35:00.566 --> 35:02.868
[Chuckles]

35:02.901 --> 35:06.338
I always forget how good
Joe is with the girls.

35:06.372 --> 35:08.474
Just really lights them
right up.

35:10.609 --> 35:12.711
Because we're a team.

35:23.189 --> 35:24.856
Hey.

35:26.825 --> 35:29.161
Hey. Sorry.

35:29.195 --> 35:30.429
You okay?

35:33.965 --> 35:37.536
This is where I found him.
I'm gonna go.

35:44.376 --> 35:46.712
[Door opens, closes]

35:52.651 --> 35:57.256
**

