37:10.929 --> 37:11.997
Hello?

37:12.030 --> 37:13.465
[Door closes]

37:13.499 --> 37:15.701
[Music plays indistinctly
in headphones]

37:15.734 --> 37:17.769
[Knock on door]

37:17.803 --> 37:20.472
Come in.

37:20.506 --> 37:24.410
Hey. Bos just showed up.
He brought food.

37:24.443 --> 37:25.977
[Sighs]

37:26.011 --> 37:29.715
Mom wanted me to see
if you needed any help.

37:29.748 --> 37:31.417
Mm.

37:31.450 --> 37:34.252
I don't really want
any of this stuff.

37:35.487 --> 37:37.789
Just my CDs
and my pictures.

37:41.059 --> 37:43.462
What?

37:43.495 --> 37:45.364
[Chuckles]

37:45.397 --> 37:46.665
What?

37:46.698 --> 37:48.834
Why didn't you apply
to college?

37:48.867 --> 37:51.437
Well, I wasn't gonna get
into any of them.

37:51.470 --> 37:53.639
[Chuckles]

37:54.973 --> 37:57.909
What are you gonna do?

37:57.943 --> 37:59.878
I don't know.

38:01.547 --> 38:04.783
I'll figure it out.

38:06.785 --> 38:08.754
Donating you.

38:08.787 --> 38:10.789
[Chuckles]
Like to see you try.

38:10.822 --> 38:13.692
[Laughs]
At least they have you.

38:15.126 --> 38:17.996
Exactly what they want
in every way.

38:19.831 --> 38:22.501
Well, not every way.

38:24.903 --> 38:26.672
Come here.

38:26.705 --> 38:28.407
Dummy.

38:31.377 --> 38:33.612
Mm.

38:33.645 --> 38:37.048
You're not gonna
go away, too, are you?

39:03.775 --> 39:07.012
Joe, you ever have
my chili?

39:07.045 --> 39:08.346
Oh, I don't know.

39:10.782 --> 39:13.919
It's an old Bosworth family
recipe, handed down.

39:16.488 --> 39:19.491
The secret's in the cinnamon.
Yeah.

39:19.525 --> 39:21.727
See, what you do is,
you take that cinnamon,

39:21.760 --> 39:23.495
and you put it
in the cupboard

39:23.529 --> 39:25.130
and keep it away
from your chili

39:25.163 --> 39:28.434
'cause it got no damn business
being there in the first place.

39:32.938 --> 39:35.106
[Sighs]

39:44.215 --> 39:47.586
You know, I remember...

39:47.619 --> 39:50.188
I didn't really even
notice Gordon

39:50.221 --> 39:55.694
until he started working
on "The Giant" with y'all.

39:55.727 --> 39:58.096
I used to call him
Soup Stain...

39:58.129 --> 40:00.165
[Chuckles]
...'cause he always had a --

40:00.198 --> 40:03.835
I'm not...

40:03.869 --> 40:06.037
ready to do that.

40:30.228 --> 40:32.631
You do me a favor
and taste this real quick?

40:32.664 --> 40:34.466
I'm not hungry.

40:34.500 --> 40:36.034
I don't care
if you're hungry.

40:36.067 --> 40:39.104
Just want to make sure
it's not too hot for the girls.

40:39.137 --> 40:41.139
They been eating crap
all week.

40:41.172 --> 40:43.809
I want to make sure
they get a good meal.

40:43.842 --> 40:46.745
Just check the damn spice level
on that, if you could.

40:46.778 --> 40:49.147
I want to make sure
everyone's gonna eat it.

40:56.287 --> 40:57.723
It's good.

40:57.756 --> 40:59.024
Not too spicy?

40:59.057 --> 41:00.726
No.

41:00.759 --> 41:02.227
It's really good.

41:02.260 --> 41:04.763
Good.

41:18.810 --> 41:20.646
[Door opens]

41:22.781 --> 41:24.015
[Door closes]

41:27.786 --> 41:29.588
Hey.

41:29.621 --> 41:31.189
The food will be ready
in a minute

41:31.222 --> 41:32.891
if you want to gather
the troops.

41:32.924 --> 41:34.159
Yeah, sure.

41:34.192 --> 41:36.928
Uh, do you know
where Cameron is?

41:36.962 --> 41:39.030
Bos: No.

41:55.280 --> 41:57.749
Hey, I just...

41:57.783 --> 42:00.118
needed a -- a minute.

42:00.151 --> 42:02.654
Yeah.

42:02.688 --> 42:05.290
Bos brought some food,
so we're gonna eat soon,

42:05.323 --> 42:07.058
if you want to join.

42:09.227 --> 42:11.963
Oh, God.

42:16.902 --> 42:19.037
This is too much.

42:19.070 --> 42:22.574
[Breathes deeply]
I didn't know...

42:22.608 --> 42:26.077
it would be this hard
to be here.

42:26.111 --> 42:28.279
[Breathes deeply]

42:28.313 --> 42:31.082
It's okay.
I didn't, um...

42:31.116 --> 42:33.351
I don't mean to make this
about me.

42:33.384 --> 42:36.154
Please,
make it about you.

42:36.187 --> 42:39.825
I feel like everybody's
been handling me.

42:39.858 --> 42:42.828
Nobody knows how to act.

42:45.631 --> 42:50.068
Well, I really love it when
people say, "How are you doing?"

42:50.101 --> 42:55.206
[Chuckles] I'm pretty sure
I asked you that.

42:55.240 --> 42:56.642
Yeah, of course you did.

42:56.675 --> 42:58.710
'Cause what else
are you gonna say?

42:58.744 --> 43:01.346
And then, yeah,
how do you answer?

43:03.181 --> 43:04.650
Hangin' in there.

43:04.683 --> 43:05.817
That's right.

43:05.851 --> 43:07.753
'Cause to answer honestly,

43:07.786 --> 43:10.822
you'd have to talk incessantly
for days,

43:10.856 --> 43:12.958
and who wants to listen
to that, right?

43:16.962 --> 43:19.130
So...

43:21.099 --> 43:22.901
How are you doing?

43:24.803 --> 43:26.938
[Chuckles]
Hangin' in there.

43:33.411 --> 43:39.350
I lost
a really good...friend.

43:44.990 --> 43:48.694
And I don't have that many
of those to spare.

43:51.730 --> 43:55.633
I know, like...poor me.

44:03.441 --> 44:06.144
But I've always had
a bit of trouble

44:06.177 --> 44:08.847
making those sorts
of connections.

44:10.348 --> 44:13.685
[Shuddered breathing]

44:13.719 --> 44:17.122
There's just not a lot
of people in my life.

44:19.424 --> 44:21.960
Me neither.

44:26.197 --> 44:28.700
Cameron:
I can't even talk to Joe.

44:28.734 --> 44:31.069
Why not?

44:33.004 --> 44:38.276
We're at...different places
in our life.

44:38.309 --> 44:44.449
This has brought up
a lot of stuff for him.

44:44.482 --> 44:46.684
Like what?

44:49.855 --> 44:52.123
He wants kids.

44:52.157 --> 44:53.992
Wow.

44:54.025 --> 44:56.294
I-I'm...

44:58.129 --> 45:00.265
If you want that,
I think you'd be great --

45:00.298 --> 45:03.068
No, I...do not.

45:03.101 --> 45:05.971
I mean, I just never have.

45:08.106 --> 45:10.475
And I don't see that
changing.

45:15.046 --> 45:17.215
Well, then don't.

45:19.918 --> 45:23.388
It's really hard,
and I...

45:24.990 --> 45:28.493
You have to really want it
to do a halfway decent job.

45:28.526 --> 45:30.762
I mean...

45:30.796 --> 45:33.198
Even then...

45:33.231 --> 45:34.532
you always wanted it.

45:34.565 --> 45:36.868
I mean, I...

45:36.902 --> 45:39.871
I didn't plan on getting
pregnant right out of school,

45:43.208 --> 45:46.411
yeah, yeah,
I-I always wanted it.

45:49.414 --> 45:54.119
And there's nothing wrong
with not feeling that way.

45:54.152 --> 45:56.487
Thank you.

46:01.559 --> 46:03.929
If you change your mind,
though,

46:03.962 --> 46:07.265
I've got a 17-year-old
I'm looking to unload, so...

46:07.298 --> 46:09.767
[Laughs] Whatever.

46:31.289 --> 46:33.992
I -- I miss him.

46:38.096 --> 46:40.465
[Sighs] So do I.

46:40.498 --> 46:45.803
**

46:48.573 --> 46:51.009
And I miss you, too.

46:51.042 --> 46:55.446
**

46:59.450 --> 47:01.486
I'm here.

47:01.519 --> 47:05.256
**

47:09.527 --> 47:14.099
**

47:14.132 --> 47:16.267
I spent so much...

47:18.336 --> 47:21.639
I spent so much time
telling him...

47:21.672 --> 47:25.076
everything he did wrong...

47:29.614 --> 47:31.917
He did a ton wrong.

47:31.950 --> 47:34.920
[Both laugh]

47:34.953 --> 47:39.958
**

47:39.991 --> 47:41.993
